Our pinnacle, Our inspiration

Our Own Sri Swamiji

Sri Swamiji is a rare Yogi – one who has embodied a new yet ancient path, paving the way for countless others to achieve peace of mind through yoga.

His Holiness is our divine guide who promotes the ancient Vedic traditions. Sri Swamiji's universal vision and deep compassion for the upliftment of the mankind has inspired the Peetham to run a vast variety of programs, activities and projects towards enrichment of human life.

Learn more

Highlights

CLASSES
Bhagavad Gita Chanting Class

Kids, youth and adults can benefit all alike by chanting the Gita. By His divine grace of His Holiness Sri Swamiji we have started Gita recitation classes. The goal is to teach all 18 chapters. Please join and take advantage of this priceless age-old blissful art of Gurukula-style Chanting.

EVENT
Remote Events & Services

During Covid-19 Pandemic, Hanuman Temple is broadcasting LIVE Festival Pujas, conducting Group Pujas, FREE Yoga classes, Spiritual Discourses and resuming Online Pujas for the sake of community and devotees.

FEATURED
Rajagopura Courtyard

A Courtyard around Rajagopura has been conceived to ease devotees entering & existing out of temple. Construction activity of this project is currently in progress. This work is expected to be completed along with a Indianized six feet wall.

Temple History

Parama Pujya Sri Swamiji met with Dallas and Houston Satsang groups on August 11th, Saturday 2007 at Datta Temple, Baton Rouge. Sri Swamiji directed devotees at that gathering to find land in Dallas to build Marakata Karya Siddhi Hanuman Temple. This will become the only Marakata (Jade) stone idol in North America/Europe.

Learn more

Cafeteria

A new 3200 sqft kitchen expansion was approved by the City of Frisco in 2016. The expanded kitchen project was completed in 2017. HH Sri Swamiji inaugurated the new kitchen during the Guru Mahotsav celebrations in December 2017.
